Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reclaimArea(25.10)                                          reclaimArea(25.10)

Name
       reclaimArea  -  Creates  space in the design by downsizing and deleting
       buffers, without worsening the slack or increasing the design rule vio-
       lations

Syntax
       reclaimArea

       [-help]

       [-maintainHold]

       [-noDeclone]

       [-noDeleteBuffer]

       [-noDownsize]

       Creates space in the design by downsizing and deleting buffers, without
       worsening the slack or increasing the design rule violations.

       Note: Cadence recommends using the optDesigncommand to  correct  timing
       violations during timing optimization instead of using this command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each  reclaimArea parameter. For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:  man reclaimArea

       -maintainHold
              Runs the hold aware area reclaim. This is only  supported  after
              the design has been routed.

       -noDeclone
              Stops  Innovus  from decloning instances to reclaim area. By de-
              fault, the software declones instances to reclaim area.

       -noDeleteBuffer
              Prohibits Innovus from deleting buffers to reclaim area.

              Default: The software deletes buffers to reclaim area.

       -noDownsize
              Prohibits Innovus from downsizing instances to reclaim area.

              Default: The software downsizes instances to reclaim area.

Example
       By default area reduction is  happening  only  on  positive  slack  in-
       stances.  To  allow  the  tool to reclaim area on instances that have a
       negative slack, you can set a negative setup target slack:

       setOptMode -opt_setup_target_slack <current_negative_slack>

       reclaimArea

